Not a candidate or interested in a surgical procedure, but looking to enhance the 🍑…⁣
⁣
Sculptra/RADIESSE BBL is an option that can subtly enhance the look of the booty. The process involves a series of injections to stimulate natural collagen growth to the buttocks. It CANNOT add the amount of volume achieved with a surgical procedure, but can create a subtle enhancement over time. ⁣
⁣
Keep in mind, Sculptra/RADIESSE BBL does require several visits over the course of a few months. Please make sure to have a conversation with your licensed provider about realistic expectations!!!💋

You are hearing the buzz about Ozempic…Everyone is on it, so what is it and how does it work. Let’s Chat💋

Ozempic is a medication used to treat type 2 diabetes, however has shown to be EXTREMELY EFFECTIVE with weight loss...

Ozempic (brand name for SEMAGLUTIDE) works by increasing the amount of insulin produced by the pancreas in response to high blood sugar levels. The medication works by increasing the levels of GLP-1, the hormone that helps regulate blood sugar levels and appetite. This can lead to decreased appetite and food intake, resulting in (you guessed it) weight loss. 

Now…you must, I repeat, YOU MUST discuss this with a licensed practitioner and make sure you are a suitable candidate!!!

So let’s face it, sometimes a surgical revision is needed. A revision is a second surgery for complications or for “unsatisfactory results”. When talking specifically about a breast surgery, a revision might be needed if:⁣
⁣
•You’re dealing with a breast implant-related issue such as capsular contracture, a condition in which hardened scar tissue can cause pain or tenderness as well as misshapen breasts.⁣
•You’d like to change the type of implants you have⁣
•Your implant ruptured⁣
•You are unhappy with your results⁣
⁣
Simply put,a revision can help correct these issues however, you will want to discuss with your board certified plastic surgeon about your options and if a revision surgery is needed💋⁣

First of all, what is a face lift? A face lift (Rhytidectomy) is a surgical procedure that aims to improve the appearance of the face and neck. The procedure involves making an incision around the hairline and ears, then lifting and tightening the underlying tissues and muscles. Excess skin is then removed and the remaining skin is redraped over the face and neck. You will find different techniques performed by different surgeons, but the most popular and widely known is the SMAS technique (Superficial Musculoaponeurotic System).⁣⁣ As we have seen in recent years, this procedure is being performed more in patients starting in late 40s to early 50s (no, you don’t have to have done at this age)!⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Recovery time for a facelift can vary, but most patients can expect to return to normal activities within two weeks.⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
REMEMBER, It's SO important to note that a facelift is a surgical procedure that requires a board certified, skilled and experienced surgeon. Potential risks and complications should be thoroughly discussed with your surgeon prior to undergoing the procedure💋⁣
⁣

To Bloc or not to Bloc…

Have you ever heard of an en bloc procedure in plastic surgery?

An en bloc procedure involves removing a breast implant and its surrounding capsule as a single unit. The capsule is the scar tissue that naturally forms around the implant after it's been inserted. By removing both the implant and capsule together, the surgeon can minimize the potential of foreign material being left behind (can also be used for facial or body implants, making it a versatile technique).

It's SUPER important to note that NOT ALL patients are candidates for en bloc procedures, and that the decision to perform this type of surgery will depend on each individual case. If you're considering breast implant removal, be sure to talk to your board certified plastic surgeon about your options and WHAT IS BEST FOR YOU and not what you read on social media💋

Do your skin a favor… 

Establish a consistent skincare routine and watch it glow up (Think about it like brushing your teeth). Taking just a few minutes in the AM and PM to care for your skin can make a huge difference in the long run. 

Don't know where to start? Here are a few tips to help you establish a skincare routine that works for you:

1️⃣ Know your skin type to choose products that are right for you.

2️⃣ Start with the basics: a gentle cleanser, moisturizer, and sunscreen. Do your routine at the same time every day to become consistent for about 12 weeks.

3️⃣After you have been able to stick with a consistent schedule with the above products, begin to add in active ingredients (ie: retinols, serums, etc) **I HIGHLY recommend seeing a licensed professional to help get you started with these type of products 

This can be a great way to practice self-care and give yourself a little boost of confidence 🧖🏼‍♀️ Remember, it's never too late to start taking care of your skin! Want more tips? Comment below 💋

Let's chat about (almost) everyone's complaint about the lower face...sagging jowls, excess fat, loose skin...shall I continue?⁣
⁣
Not ready for surgery, but ready to dive into ways to help correct? Noninvasive chin and jawline contouring can address and correct through a combination of different treatments. Now, certain things won't be for everyone, but here's the rundown:⁣
⭐️ DERMAL FILLERS- When strategically injected, FILLERS can create a more defined jawline⁣
⭐️ WRINKLE RELAXERS - any neurotoxin (ie: botox, dysport, jeaveau) injected into the neck and /or jawline to relax the muscle helping to define the jawline and improve the appearance of the neck band muscles.⁣
⭐️ KYBELLA - if you suffer from submental fullness AKA, double chin and want to avoid surgery, an injection that breaks down fat cells, which are then gradually absorbed by the body and flushed away over time.⁣
⭐️ THREADS- This deserves a post of its own- lift, pull, smooth…voila⁣
⭐️ RF MICRONEEDLING- lifts, tightens and contours skin laxity on the face (and body)...And the best part, as time passes, collagen continues to produce and you'll continue to see results up to 3 months⁣
***The results after nonsurgical jawline contouring can vary and MUST you be reminded, please discuss with a licensed provider (multiple treatments might will be necessary for upkeep)⁣

IPL (Intense Pulse Light) aka “fotofacial or photofacial”, is for treatments of vascular conditions (“spider veins”) and brown spots (“age spots”) caused by sun damage. IPL stimulates the production of collagen, which plumps up the skin to give a fresher look and refines or tightens large pores. This treatment is used to improve the appearance of the face, neck, hands and body by reducing excessive red and brown tones in the skin. Also amazing for Small broken capillaries or superficial blood vessels, skin tone/texture, fine lines, and so much more! ⁣
⁣
Let’s not forget every patient is unique and MUST be evaluated by a licensed provider to determine which treatment would work best for their skin type and tone💋⁣

Scars post procedure…Swipe👉🏼 ⁣
The formation of scars is a totally normal part of the recovery process. As our skin repairs itself, collagen is produced, binding the wound together and gradually forming scar tissue. Over time, the scar will undergo transformations (changes in color, texture, and overall appearance). BE PATIENT…depending on the individual patient, the scar will typically turn into a barely visible white line (remember, I said depending on the individual patient). Take care of your scars, listen to your BOARD CERTIFIED plastic surgeon’s recommendations, and USE SUN PROTECTION💋

Tummy Time…mini vs full tummy tuck💋

𝗠𝗶𝗻𝗶 𝗧𝘂𝗰𝗸
•Not everyone is a candidate
•Only addesses the loose skin under the belly button
•No muscle wall tightening…well, not always
•The belly button remains the same
•Typically, same incision and size of incision as full tummy tuck

𝗙𝘂𝗹𝗹 𝗧𝘂𝗺𝗺𝘆 𝗧𝘂𝗰𝗸
•Incision from hip to hip
•Abdominal wall tightening
•Excess skin/fat from the upper and lower abdomen are removed
•A new hole for the belly button is created (no, the belly button is not removed)

Eyes, Eyes Baby…👁️ procedures

If you have already tried fillers or other undereye non-surgical procedures, it might be time to consider eyelid surgery. A blepharoplasty, is a cosmetic surgery that can be performed on the upper and/or lower eyelids.

Because the skin around your eyes is the thinnest and most delicate, signs of aging appear faster here than in other areas of your body. Aging can contribute to the loss of elasticity, which then causes the skin around your eyes to sag and droop. Bags under your eyes can make you look angry, sad, or tired (you always look tired, but you aren't tired…sound familiar??).

The goal is to create an eyelid that is more open and alert as well as a smooth contour from your lower lash line down to your midface. You can also add volume to your cheek area with fillers to complete the smooth transition from your eyelids to your cheeks. Voilá...more youthful appearance and finally a well rested face

PS: for the love of all things aesthetics and beauty, pleaseee, consult with a board certified plastic surgeon to see if this is right for you💋

I’ve said it before and I’ll say it again for those in the back… Pilates...and why you should do it (you too, gents):⁣
⁣
I can attest to the AMAZING benefits of adding Pilates to your existing exercise regimen OR to those who don't workout:⁣
⁣
-Engages both the larger muscles and the smaller stabilizing muscles, resulting in a full-body workout that improves overall strength, flexibility, and coordination.⁣
-Core strength and stability: Pilates emphasizes the activation of the deep core muscles, such as the abdominals and back muscles. Many people who are inactive often struggle with weak core muscles and poor posture. Pilates targets these areas specifically, helping to strengthen the core, improve postural alignment, and alleviate back pain or discomfort caused by sedentary habits.⁣
- Increased flexibility: The combination of stretching and strengthening movements helps to lengthen muscles, improve range of motion, and reduce muscle imbalances. ⁣
- Low impact and joint friendly: when on a reformer, the sliding carriage and the springs provide resistance without putting excessive stress on the joints, making it suitable for individuals with ioint issues or those recovering from injuries. It ALSO allows to gradually build strength and flexibilit without putting excessive strain on your body. This can be especially beneficial for people who spend long hours sitting.⁣
- Stress reduction and relaxation: Pilates requires concentration, control, and precision of movement. This aspect of the practice helps to develop body awareness, focus, and a sense of mindfulness during exercise.⁣
⁣
So basically, it's good for everyone and I PROMISE you will love💋

Bustling Choices…

In the world of breast surgery, it's not just about size—it's also about profile.

The term "profile" refers to the outward projection or shape of the breast implant once it is placed within the breast tissue. It determines how much the implant extends from the chest wall, influencing the overall appearance and silhouette of the breasts. Different implant profiles offer varying degrees of projection, allowing individuals to achieve different looks, from subtle and natural to more pronounced (a more “augmented” look). The profile helps create the desired contour and fullness of the breasts, contributing to the overall aesthetic outcome of the breast augmentation procedure.

Whether you're looking for subtle enhancement, the “did she/ didn’t she” balancing act, or the 👀 look,  different breast implant profiles offer a wide array of choices to cater to your desired outcome. After all, it's your canvas—paint it with the “profile” that speak to you.

Your plastic surgery journey doesn't end in the operating room— it's just the beginning. I can't stress enough the importance of adopting a healthy lifestyle post-surgery. Your surgery is only a small part of the process…YOU have to put in the work post op. By embracing a healthy lifestyle, you will enjoy long lasting results, but also safeguard your investment 💋

Common Plastic Surgery Myths Debunked 

Myth: "Plastic surgery results look unnatural."
Fact: Modern techniques emphasize natural-looking results. Skilled board certified plastic surgeons prioritize harmony and balance, so you can enhance your beauty while looking like the best version of yourself….BUT, it is also OK if you are looking for a more “unnatural” look💋

Myth: "Plastic surgery is a shortcut to diet and exercise."
Fact: Surgery complements a healthy lifestyle but isn't a substitute. As discussed in a previous post, exercise and nutrition are essential for long-term results

Myth : "Plastic surgery is only for women."
Fact: Men also benefit from plastic surgery, seeking procedures to boost confidence and appearance.

And of course your friendly reminder…ALWAYSSS consult with a board-certified surgeon to address your specific needs and concerns

You call it football season…in my world, it’s 𝑳𝒊𝒑𝒐𝒔𝒖𝒄𝒕𝒊𝒐𝒏 season💋⁣
⁣
Liposuction can eliminate trouble spots on your thighs, hips, abdomen, under the chin... basically anywhere. However, it is important to educate yourself, because an informed patient is a happy patient🤗⁣
⁣⁣⁣
𝐋𝐢𝐩𝐨𝐬𝐮𝐜𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐢𝐬 𝐧𝐨𝐭 𝐚 𝐟𝐚𝐬𝐭 𝐰𝐚𝐲 𝐭𝐨 𝐚 𝐟𝐢𝐭 𝐛𝐨𝐝𝐲. It’s important to recognize that liposuction is not a weight loss procedure, so you should not expect to lose a dramatic amount of weight. However, because liposuction strategically removes fat from predefined areas of the body, it can provide significant cosmetic improvements. Additionally, liposuction has the potential to make your clothes fit better and boost your confidence.⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
𝐆𝐨𝐨𝐝 𝐜𝐚𝐧𝐝𝐢𝐝𝐚𝐭𝐞𝐬 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐥𝐢𝐩𝐨𝐬𝐮𝐜𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐚𝐫𝐞 𝐜𝐥𝐨𝐬𝐞 𝐭𝐨 𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐢𝐫 𝐢𝐝𝐞𝐚𝐥 𝐰𝐞𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐭. Because liposuction won’t necessarily change the number on the scale by much, it is important to be as close to your goal weight before the procedure. Liposuction is not a replacement for living a healthy lifestyle, but instead is designed to reduce stubborn pockets of fat that are resistant to diet and exercise. Therefore it’s a good idea to form and maintain healthy eating and workout habits to optimize your results💋

Who is Beautyinplastics and what do I actually do…

Besides “managing” multiple practices (and teaching pilates), I’m also “your favorite patient care coordinator”. Anddd what does that mean…
I work closely with patients, offering tailored guidance from the first consultation to post-op recovery. I help navigate options, educate about procedures of interest, provide support, and ensure a seamless experience💋

As your favorite plastic surgery coordinator, here are some questions to ask your (BOARD👏🏼CERTIFIED) plastic surgeon during your consultation:⁣
⁣
1. Are you board certified in plastic surgery?⁣
2. How much experience do you have performing the procedure I am considering?⁣
3. What are the risks and potential complications associated with the procedure? How do you handle?⁣
4. What type of anesthesia will be used, and who will administer it?⁣
5. What is the recovery process like, and how long will it take?⁣
6. Can you show me before-and-after photos of patients who have had the same procedure?⁣
6. What is the cost of the procedure, and what does it include?⁣
⁣
Choosing to undergo plastic surgery is a big decision (and an expensive one), and finding the right plastic surgeon is essential to ensure that you achieve the results you desire💋⁣
